00:22:08,928 --> 00:22:10,597
Well, actually...

256
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:11,964
Here, let me help you with this.

257
00:22:11,998 --> 00:22:14,467
Actually I kind of had something else in mind.

258
00:22:14,501 --> 00:22:16,469
I... I think you're going to like it though.

259
00:22:16,503 --> 00:22:18,838
Oh, okay.

260
00:22:24,977 --> 00:22:26,946
It's really a beautiful place you got here.

261
00:22:26,979 --> 00:22:28,915
Oh thanks. It was my grandmother's.

262
00:22:28,948 --> 00:22:30,750
She left it to me.

263
00:22:30,783 --> 00:22:32,785
I couldn't afford this on my own.

264
00:22:35,154 --> 00:22:37,857
- Wait.
- What are you doing?

265
00:22:37,890 --> 00:22:40,793
I'm gonna take you someplace
you’ve never been before.

266
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,569
Uh, thanks.

267
00:22:49,602 --> 00:22:52,104
Oh my.

268
00:22:52,138 --> 00:22:54,774
This is an unpretentious and intimate little place

269
00:22:54,807 --> 00:22:57,510
that I like to call cafe Ming Costello.

270
00:22:57,544 --> 00:22:59,145
- ( laughs )
- Would you like to sit down?

271
00:22:59,178 --> 00:23:02,482
Oh yes, please. Thank you.

272
00:23:02,515 --> 00:23:04,917
This is lovely.

273
00:23:04,951 --> 00:23:08,020
It's a bit cold, but it's very picturesque.

274
00:23:08,054 --> 00:23:12,825
- A little mood music for us.
- ( flute sonata playing )

275
00:23:12,859 --> 00:23:15,061
Actually the owner is a friend of mine.

276
00:23:15,094 --> 00:23:16,763
This place is usually jammed,

277
00:23:16,796 --> 00:23:19,932
but I slipped him a Franklin
and the place is ours.

278
00:23:19,966 --> 00:23:21,834
It certainly is.

279
00:23:21,868 --> 00:23:24,771
Oh, I hope you like Szechuan food.

280
00:23:24,804 --> 00:23:26,873
I took the liberty of buying everything.

281
00:23:26,906 --> 00:23:30,477
- I love Szechuan.
- ( siren blaring )

282
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:33,980
- For you.
- Thank you.

283
00:23:35,882 --> 00:23:38,951
So tell me, Mr. Costello,

284
00:23:38,985 --> 00:23:41,654
what made you want to go out with me so badly

285
00:23:41,688 --> 00:23:43,990
that you dropped my class?

286
00:23:44,023 --> 00:23:45,958
Well, I think it was the combination

287
00:23:45,992 --> 00:23:49,996
of your fabulous teaching technique,

288
00:23:50,029 --> 00:23:53,800
your leadership, insightful criticism,

289
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:56,035
sparkling smile,

290
00:23:56,068 --> 00:23:59,038
- incredible legs...
- Please.

291
00:23:59,071 --> 00:24:00,907
( helicopter whirring )

292
00:24:06,813 --> 00:24:08,815
( laughing )

293
00:24:12,652 --> 00:24:16,188
- Oh, let me take this from you.
- Oh thanks.

294
00:24:17,924 --> 00:24:20,893
So can I see you tomorrow night?

295
00:24:20,927 --> 00:24:23,863
Patrick, I like you. I really do.

296
00:24:23,896 --> 00:24:26,499
I sense a "but" coming.

297
00:24:26,533 --> 00:24:28,635
Well, I've been seeing someone.

298
00:24:28,668 --> 00:24:29,936
You've been seeing someone?

299
00:24:29,969 --> 00:24:31,671
Or you've sort of been seeing someone,

300
00:24:31,704 --> 00:24:34,040
or you're unbelievably,
incredibly involved with someone, what?

301
00:24:34,073 --> 00:24:36,008
I don't know. It's new.

302
00:24:36,042 --> 00:24:38,545
I mean he's older. He's mature.

303
00:24:38,578 --> 00:24:40,012
He's very stable.

304
00:24:40,046 --> 00:24:43,950
- Incredibly boring?
- Definitely not boring.

305
00:24:43,983 --> 00:24:46,919
So, um, I get the picture.

306
00:24:46,953 --> 00:24:48,521
I guess tomorrow night’s out then.

307
00:24:48,555 --> 00:24:50,757
I didn't say that.

308
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:52,525
No, you didn't.

309
00:24:52,559 --> 00:24:54,026
Can we talk about it tomorrow?

310
00:24:54,060 --> 00:24:56,863
I don't see why not.

311
00:25:13,312 --> 00:25:15,014
Good night.

312
00:25:15,047 --> 00:25:18,017
- I'll call you tomorrow.
- Okay.

313
00:25:36,869 --> 00:25:39,806
woman: Get your hands off me!

314
00:25:39,839 --> 00:25:42,809
No! Help me!

315
00:25:42,842 --> 00:25:44,844
Hold up your gun, Frank.

316
00:25:48,347 --> 00:25:51,183
No! Help me!

317
00:25:54,386 --> 00:25:57,289
Bill, help me!

318
00:25:58,290 --> 00:26:01,027
( snoring )

319
00:26:02,261 --> 00:26:04,130
Pfft.

320
00:26:44,070 --> 00:26:45,772
( metal rasping )

321
00:26:55,181 --> 00:26:57,884
Don't you know it’s impolite to stare?

322
00:27:00,953 --> 00:27:03,756
Don't you know it's impolite to stare?

323
00:27:03,790 --> 00:27:06,392
Hmm.

324
00:27:08,695 --> 00:27:10,062
( screams )

325
00:27:10,096 --> 00:27:13,933
Somebody please! Help me!

326
00:27:13,966 --> 00:27:18,004
( choking, coughing )

327
00:27:46,933 --> 00:27:48,300
( banging on door )

328
00:27:48,334 --> 00:27:51,003
( gasps )

329
00:27:51,037 --> 00:27:53,372
Nick: Yeah, yeah, I'm coming.

330
00:27:53,405 --> 00:27:56,075
I'm coming. Jesus.

331
00:27:56,108 --> 00:27:59,478
- Costello.
- ( banging )

332
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:02,081
What? yeah, just a minute.

333
00:28:03,515 --> 00:28:07,053
Costello, I thought you were in bed, man.

334
00:28:07,086 --> 00:28:10,790
Aw, Jesus.

335
00:28:10,823 --> 00:28:12,291
Come on, man, wake up.

336
00:28:16,963 --> 00:28:19,331
Come on, man, wake up.

337
00:28:19,365 --> 00:28:22,869
( panting )

338
00:28:22,902 --> 00:28:25,071
- Nick, what's going on?
- "What's going on"?

339
00:28:25,104 --> 00:28:27,073
Are you serious?

340
00:28:27,106 --> 00:28:29,375
You're sleepwalking again, for Christ's sake.

341
00:28:29,408 --> 00:28:30,977
You're even dressing for it.

342
00:28:31,010 --> 00:28:33,345
- You're dangerous, man.
- I'm sorry, man.

343
00:28:33,379 --> 00:28:36,115
Yeah well, do me a favor
and do yourself a favor...

344
00:28:36,148 --> 00:28:38,751
Go see someone.

345
00:28:38,785 --> 00:28:40,987
Get a prescription.

346
00:28:44,991 --> 00:28:46,959
( honks )

347
00:29:07,046 --> 00:29:09,015
- Patrick.
- Hi, Laurel.

348
00:29:09,048 --> 00:29:10,850
Can I speak to you for a sec?

349
00:29:10,883 --> 00:29:13,119
Um, this isn’t a good time.

350
00:29:13,152 --> 00:29:14,987
It's kind of important.

351
00:29:15,021 --> 00:29:17,957
Well, actually, Patrick,
I'm in the middle of a meeting.

352
00:29:17,990 --> 00:29:20,993
- That's okay. I'll just take a second.
- No, it's not okay.

353
00:29:21,027 --> 00:29:23,229
I'm busy. There's someone here.

354
00:29:23,262 --> 00:29:25,798
Okay, okay.

355
00:29:25,832 --> 00:29:28,134
I'll just tell you out here then.

356
00:29:28,167 --> 00:29:31,237
Uh, it's kind of hard to explain,

357
00:29:31,270 --> 00:29:33,472
but there's this man

358
00:29:33,505 --> 00:29:34,573
and he lives in this building.

359
00:29:34,606 --> 00:29:37,176
And I just get a really weird feeling about him.

360
00:29:37,209 --> 00:29:40,146
- I think you should stay away from him.
- What man?

361
00:29:40,179 --> 00:29:43,082
- Professor Steering.
- What?

362
00:29:43,115 --> 00:29:45,551
Laurel, is that for me?

363
00:29:45,584 --> 00:29:48,988
No, Ted, it's for me.

364
00:29:49,021 --> 00:29:51,557
If you don't mind, this'll just take a minute.

365
00:29:57,129 --> 00:29:59,165
What the hell’s going on here, Patrick?

366
00:30:02,634 --> 00:30:04,270
So that's Ted, huh?

367
00:30:04,303 --> 00:30:06,105
That's the guy you’ve been seeing?

368
00:30:06,138 --> 00:30:09,475
Yes, that's right.

369
00:30:09,508 --> 00:30:11,477
Now if you don't mind...

370
00:30:11,510 --> 00:30:14,847
- Laurel.
- What?

371
00:30:16,082 --> 00:30:18,084
Forget it.

372
00:30:36,068 --> 00:30:39,071
( phones ringing, chatter )

373
00:30:49,181 --> 00:30:51,317
I need some information on the homicide case

374
00:30:51,350 --> 00:30:53,052
of the guy who’s strangling women.

375
00:30:53,085 --> 00:30:54,453
Do you know who’s handling that?

376
00:30:56,622 --> 00:30:59,258
Excuse me, are you Detective Markowitz?

377
00:30:59,291 --> 00:31:00,960
Yeah yeah, can I do something for you?

378
00:31:00,993 --> 00:31:02,594
- Hi, I'm Patrick Costello.
- Uh-huh.

379
00:31:02,628 --> 00:31:04,563
- I have some information for you.
- That's great.

380
00:31:04,596 --> 00:31:07,133
- Look, just sit down right over here, okay?
- Okay, thanks.

381
00:31:07,166 --> 00:31:09,335
So what kind of information?

382
00:31:09,368 --> 00:31:13,272
It's about this case that you guys are
working on... the guy who kills women.

383
00:31:13,305 --> 00:31:15,607
What kind of information, Mr. Costello?

384
00:31:15,641 --> 00:31:17,944
I think I saw the killer.

385
00:31:17,977 --> 00:31:19,979
How do you know he’s the killer?

386
00:31:20,012 --> 00:31:22,081
He was in a car and he was strangling a woman.

387
00:31:22,114 --> 00:31:25,084
- Where was the car?
- I'm not exactly sure.

388
00:31:25,117 --> 00:31:28,087
- I think on the waterfront maybe.
- Where on the Waterfront?

389
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:29,488
I just told you I’m not exactly sure.

390
00:31:29,521 --> 00:31:32,324
You're telling me you saw
some guy killing some lady

391
00:31:32,358 --> 00:31:34,026
and you don't know where it was?

392
00:31:34,060 --> 00:31:36,328
I can give you a description of the man.

393
00:31:36,362 --> 00:31:38,364
How come you don't know where it was?

394
00:31:40,132 --> 00:31:42,034
Well, how is it you don't know where it was?

395
00:31:42,068 --> 00:31:44,403
( sighs )

396
00:31:44,436 --> 00:31:48,140
- I'm a psychic.
- A psychic?

397
00:31:50,009 --> 00:31:52,378
Got some clippings here,

398
00:31:52,411 --> 00:31:55,114
articles that were written about me.

399
00:31:57,383 --> 00:31:59,185
Oh yeah, Patrick Costello.

400
00:31:59,218 --> 00:32:02,054
Oh, Child Psychic, yes.

401
00:32:02,088 --> 00:32:04,723
This is fascinating.

402
00:32:04,756 --> 00:32:08,694
Maybe you can give us a practical demonstration.

403
00:32:08,727 --> 00:32:10,229
What am I thinking?

404
00:32:10,262 --> 00:32:12,965
Well, it doesn't exactly work that way.

405
00:32:12,999 --> 00:32:15,567
Come on, Costello,
you gotta give us something to go on.

406
00:32:15,601 --> 00:32:19,005
How does it work, Costello?

407
00:32:19,038 --> 00:32:20,372
Well, you see, I see things.

408
00:32:20,406 --> 00:32:22,508
Sometimes it happens when I touch something,

409
00:32:22,541 --> 00:32:24,476
other times... I don't know, it just happens.

410
00:32:24,510 --> 00:32:26,045
You know, it just comes to me.

411
00:32:26,078 --> 00:32:28,614
All right, look, here's my lighter.

412
00:32:28,647 --> 00:32:32,418
Now you tell me what kind of car I drive.

413
00:32:38,457 --> 00:32:40,126
A red Camaro?

414
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,362
Look, you're just wasting my time, kid.

415
00:32:43,395 --> 00:32:45,364
Hey, come on, he was half right. It is red.

416
00:32:45,397 --> 00:32:47,699
Look, it doesn’t always happen
when I want it to, okay?

417
00:32:47,733 --> 00:32:49,435
It's kind of hard to do it under pressure.

418
00:32:49,468 --> 00:32:52,138
Well, thanks very much for dropping
by, Mr. Costello.

419
00:32:52,171 --> 00:32:55,074
And you... you stay in touch, okay?

420
00:32:55,107 --> 00:32:58,244
Look, I'm not some kind of crackpot, okay?
I saw this guy.

421
00:32:58,277 --> 00:33:00,512
I also saw the victim. I can describe her to you.

422
00:33:00,546 --> 00:33:01,680
She was in her early 20s.

423
00:33:01,713 --> 00:33:05,017
She had long, wavy reddish hair.
She was Caucasian.

424
00:33:05,051 --> 00:33:06,352
She also... she had this tattoo.

425
00:33:06,385 --> 00:33:08,420
It was like roses on her chest and...

426
00:33:08,454 --> 00:33:10,522
none of the victims had a tattoo.

427
00:33:10,556 --> 00:33:14,293
Maybe he just killed her.
Maybe you guys haven’t found the body yet.

428
00:33:14,326 --> 00:33:16,028
Maybe you'd just better get out of here

429
00:33:16,062 --> 00:33:18,130
before I throw you out, okay?

430
00:33:25,371 --> 00:33:27,339
I think you hurt his feelings.

431
00:33:27,373 --> 00:33:30,776
Aw, poor baby.

432
00:33:30,809 --> 00:33:34,413
Yo, Costello.

433
00:33:34,446 --> 00:33:38,217
Listen, I'm curious about something.

434
00:33:38,250 --> 00:33:42,054
This crime scene that you think you saw,

435
00:33:42,088 --> 00:33:44,523
is there anything about it? Anything that might...

436
00:33:44,556 --> 00:33:47,126
help you identify it?

437
00:33:47,159 --> 00:33:49,128
Listen, I've been over it so many times.

438
00:33:49,161 --> 00:33:50,829
I've told you everything.

439
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:53,265
Any buildings?

440
00:33:53,299 --> 00:33:57,169
- Actually, yeah, I think so.
- Any distinctive features?

441
00:33:57,203 --> 00:34:00,339
I'm sorry, I just can't remember.

442
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:01,840
Okay, all right.

443
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:06,078
Well listen, if you do, give me a holler, huh?

444
00:34:06,112 --> 00:34:08,347
- Yeah sure.
- All right.

445
00:34:10,182 --> 00:34:13,219
I'm telling you, Nick, I know what I saw.

446
00:34:13,252 --> 00:34:15,387
Yeah okay, but how do you know it's for real?

447
00:34:15,421 --> 00:34:18,424
I mean you were dreaming, for Christ's sake.

448
00:34:20,192 --> 00:34:22,228
Look, this guy Steering, eh?

449
00:34:22,261 --> 00:34:24,230
He's the guy she’s going out with, right?

450
00:34:24,263 --> 00:34:27,099
- Yeah, so?
- So it's natural. You're bummed.

451
00:34:27,133 --> 00:34:30,536
You can't stand the guy,
so you start dreaming that he's a killer.

452
00:34:30,569 --> 00:34:33,339
No, you see, the night I dreamed about Steering...

453
00:34:33,372 --> 00:34:36,375
that was before I met him at Laurel's apartment.

454
00:34:36,408 --> 00:34:37,876
Yeah, but you said you saw him

455
00:34:37,909 --> 00:34:41,213
- in the building once before.
- Yeah, so? But...

456
00:34:41,247 --> 00:34:43,882
Look, Nick, I'm telling you I know he's the guy.

457
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:47,653
- He's the one.
- Come on, admit it. You don't like the guy.

458
00:34:47,686 --> 00:34:51,223
But murder? Jesus.

459
00:34:51,257 --> 00:34:55,294
- Have you seen a doctor yet?
- A doctor?

460
00:34:55,327 --> 00:34:58,297
Yeah, a doctor, about that sleepwalking problem.

461
00:34:58,330 --> 00:35:01,267
No. Don't worry, I will.

462
00:35:03,902 --> 00:35:06,338
Yeah. Come on.

463
00:35:54,553 --> 00:35:56,755
It's very nice of you, but I don't do it.

464
00:35:56,788 --> 00:35:59,191
- I'm closed.
- Sorry.

465
00:36:11,903 --> 00:36:14,906
( needle buzzing )

466
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:23,882
Hi, is there somebody who could... Thanks.

467
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:31,890
Hello?

468
00:36:31,923 --> 00:36:33,925
Greetings.

469
00:36:36,862 --> 00:36:40,399
Hi, I was wondering,
have you given this tattoo to anyone

470
00:36:40,432 --> 00:36:44,336
like a young lady, say, in the last six months?

471
00:36:44,370 --> 00:36:47,639
A tattoo cannot be given. It is transferred.

472
00:36:47,673 --> 00:36:49,541
I'm only the medium.

473
00:36:50,842 --> 00:36:52,978
Of course, I understand.

474
00:36:53,011 --> 00:36:54,980
Do you think you could help me out though?

475
00:36:55,013 --> 00:36:57,916
I think I knew this woman before...

476
00:36:57,949 --> 00:36:59,851
In a previous life.

477
00:36:59,885 --> 00:37:01,987
Just a minute.

478
00:37:07,859 --> 00:37:12,564
April, April Harris.

479
00:37:12,598 --> 00:37:14,966
I transferred such a tattoo to April Harris

480
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:17,736
on the Autumn equinox,

481
00:37:17,769 --> 00:37:20,339
a very propitious day.

482
00:37:22,007 --> 00:37:24,843
Perhaps I have a design that you would enjoy.

483
00:37:31,016 --> 00:37:33,018
( baby crying )

484
00:37:56,442 --> 00:37:58,944
- Yeah?
- Hi, is April Harris here?

485
00:37:58,977 --> 00:38:01,713
- No.
- Well... excuse me. Excuse me.

486
00:38:01,747 --> 00:38:04,850
- Do you know where she is?
- No.

487
00:38:04,883 --> 00:38:07,419
Look, I'm sorry to bother you,

488
00:38:07,453 --> 00:38:09,054
but it's really important.

489
00:38:09,087 --> 00:38:11,357
When was the last time you saw her?

490
00:38:11,390 --> 00:38:15,994
I'm not sure. A couple of days anyway.

491
00:38:17,963 --> 00:38:20,466
You see her, you tell her rent's due.

492
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:44,956
( ringing )

493
00:38:44,990 --> 00:38:47,959
- Hi.
- Hello, Patrick. It's Laurel.

494
00:38:47,993 --> 00:38:50,128
<i>This is Patrick. Nick and I aren't in now.</i>

495
00:38:50,161 --> 00:38:52,998
<i>If you wanna leave a message, you know what to do.</i>

496
00:39:09,548 --> 00:39:12,584
( door opens )

497
00:39:12,618 --> 00:39:14,453
( closes )

498
00:39:20,892 --> 00:39:23,895
( doorknob rattling )

499
00:39:56,728 --> 00:39:59,397
( dog barking )

500
00:40:21,186 --> 00:40:22,921
( thuds )

501
00:40:34,199 --> 00:40:37,068
- ( glass shatters )
- Shit!

502
00:41:03,995 --> 00:41:06,865
( metal rasping )

503
00:41:16,942 --> 00:41:17,943
( screams )

504
00:41:17,976 --> 00:41:19,745
Who the hell are you

505
00:41:19,778 --> 00:41:21,613
and what are you doing in my room?

506
00:41:21,647 --> 00:41:22,914
April Harris?

507
00:41:22,948 --> 00:41:25,551
Yeah, that's right.

508
00:41:25,584 --> 00:41:27,753
Who the hell are you?

509
00:41:27,786 --> 00:41:29,555
What happened to your hair?

510
00:41:29,588 --> 00:41:32,758
- Okay, I'm calling the cops.
- No, no, no, no, wait.

511
00:41:32,791 --> 00:41:36,828
Um... you're okay.

512
00:41:36,862 --> 00:41:38,630
Yeah, of course I’m all right.

513
00:41:38,664 --> 00:41:41,867
