Maybe they'll find something else.

761
01:00:59,824 --> 01:01:01,826
- You never know.
- No.

762
01:01:14,939 --> 01:01:16,941
Excuse me.

763
01:01:16,974 --> 01:01:20,044
( birds screeching )

764
01:02:05,389 --> 01:02:07,091
( April screams )

765
01:02:10,427 --> 01:02:11,962
woman: And then when I came back in,

766
01:02:11,996 --> 01:02:13,931
she was talking with the same guy.

767
01:02:13,964 --> 01:02:15,232
She was arguing.

768
01:02:15,265 --> 01:02:17,101
And she said that she didn't know him.

769
01:02:17,134 --> 01:02:19,469
She said that he broke in.

770
01:02:19,503 --> 01:02:22,873
Now this guy, would you recognize
him if you saw him again?

771
01:02:22,907 --> 01:02:24,174
Yeah, I just saw him.

772
01:02:24,208 --> 01:02:25,943
He walked out of here 10 minutes ago.

773
01:02:25,976 --> 01:02:27,111
- Where, in the elevator?
- Yeah.

774
01:02:27,144 --> 01:02:29,446
- Hey, Adam, Adam.
- Yeah?

775
01:02:29,479 --> 01:02:31,882
Got a match on Costello’s prints.

776
01:02:31,916 --> 01:02:34,184
They're all over the dead girl's bedroom.

777
01:02:34,218 --> 01:02:35,886
( phone clacks )

778
01:02:35,920 --> 01:02:37,187
( banging on door )

779
01:02:37,221 --> 01:02:38,956
- Yeah, what? Hey!
- Adam: Come on!

780
01:02:38,989 --> 01:02:42,526
Hey, take it easy. What?

781
01:02:42,559 --> 01:02:45,029
Yeah, what... Hey, what the hell are you doing?

782
01:02:45,062 --> 01:02:47,164
- You can't just bust in here...
- This says we can.

783
01:02:47,197 --> 01:02:49,066
- What's that?
- It's a warrant.

784
01:02:49,099 --> 01:02:51,001
- A warrant for what?
- Check his room, in here.

785
01:02:51,035 --> 01:02:54,004
- Costello's apartment.
- You think Costello’s done something?

786
01:02:54,038 --> 01:02:55,339
Let me tell you something, Sonny,

787
01:02:55,372 --> 01:02:57,942
your roomie's not such a great
guy once you get to know him.

788
01:02:57,975 --> 01:03:01,345
Holy shit. What are... What are you looking for?

789
01:03:01,378 --> 01:03:04,214
- Hey, get... Come on, man.
- Listen, your friend into jewelry, huh?

790
01:03:04,248 --> 01:03:05,950
- What?
- Into jewelry, I said.

791
01:03:05,983 --> 01:03:07,417
- You ever seen this before?
- What?

792
01:03:07,451 --> 01:03:09,019
- Huh?
- No. What is it? I've never seen it.

793
01:03:09,053 --> 01:03:10,487
Go sit down and read a magazine, kid.

794
01:03:10,520 --> 01:03:12,389
- Hey, look, it's my place...
- I said sit down!

795
01:03:12,422 --> 01:03:14,424
All right. Jesus.

796
01:03:19,897 --> 01:03:22,466
Hey, what the hell’s going on here?

797
01:03:22,499 --> 01:03:24,969
- Patrick Costello, you're under arrest.
- For what?

798
01:03:25,002 --> 01:03:26,603
- ( thuds )
- Nick: Hey!

799
01:03:26,636 --> 01:03:28,205
- Keep your hands off him.
- I said sit down.

800
01:03:28,238 --> 01:03:30,340
- Okay, fine.
- Adam: Sorry about that.

801
01:03:30,374 --> 01:03:33,277
- For murder.
- What do you mean murder?

802
01:03:33,310 --> 01:03:35,279
Ricky: All right,
you got the right to remain silent.

803
01:03:35,312 --> 01:03:38,115
Anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court of law.

804
01:03:38,148 --> 01:03:39,283
You have the right to an attorney.

805
01:03:39,316 --> 01:03:41,418
If you cannot afford an
attorney, one will be provided.

806
01:03:41,451 --> 01:03:42,953
You understand these rights?

807
01:03:42,987 --> 01:03:45,489
Adam: Clear out, guys.

808
01:03:47,457 --> 01:03:50,060
Come on, get outta here.

809
01:04:15,052 --> 01:04:17,254
All right, hit the lights.

810
01:04:27,231 --> 01:04:29,466
Number two.

811
01:04:32,036 --> 01:04:34,571
He's the one. Number two.

812
01:04:34,604 --> 01:04:38,976
- Number two. Now you're sure?
- Yeah.

813
01:04:39,009 --> 01:04:41,511
- Okay, thank you very much.
- Thanks a lot.

814
01:04:46,116 --> 01:04:48,185
( door opens )

815
01:04:50,487 --> 01:04:53,924
Mr. Costello?

816
01:04:55,025 --> 01:04:58,362
I'm Randolph Fitzgerald.

817
01:04:58,395 --> 01:05:01,231
I'll be representing you in court.

818
01:05:02,566 --> 01:05:04,534
I gotta be honest with you.

819
01:05:04,568 --> 01:05:09,139
I don't think we have a very good situation here.

820
01:05:09,173 --> 01:05:11,075
I think we should have

821
01:05:11,108 --> 01:05:13,310
a nice frank discussion about it.

822
01:05:13,343 --> 01:05:15,045
I didn't do it.

823
01:05:15,079 --> 01:05:19,249
- Excuse me?
- I just said I didn't do it.

824
01:05:19,283 --> 01:05:23,954
Okay, Mr. Costello, there's a doctor arriving

825
01:05:23,988 --> 01:05:26,023
to do a little psychological evaluation

826
01:05:26,056 --> 01:05:29,226
of your fitness to stand trial.

827
01:05:29,259 --> 01:05:31,628
Mr. Costello, this is Dr....

828
01:05:31,661 --> 01:05:33,630
We've already met. Thank you, Counselor.

829
01:05:35,665 --> 01:05:37,401
Coffee?

830
01:05:42,672 --> 01:05:46,143
Before we go any further, Mr. Costello,

831
01:05:46,176 --> 01:05:48,979
I want you to know that I think you're innocent.

832
01:05:49,013 --> 01:05:52,082
I also understand that you don't
share the same feeling about me.

833
01:05:52,116 --> 01:05:56,020
Detective Spencer told me about your visions.

834
01:05:57,387 --> 01:05:59,089
Sugar?

835
01:06:01,158 --> 01:06:05,162
Now I don't believe in so-called
psychic phenomena per se,

836
01:06:05,195 --> 01:06:07,664
but I do believe that you saw
what you claimed to have seen...

837
01:06:07,697 --> 01:06:11,335
Not in a vision and not in a dream,

838
01:06:11,368 --> 01:06:14,104
but in person.

839
01:06:15,572 --> 01:06:17,407
I believe that you were actually present

840
01:06:17,441 --> 01:06:20,177
when one or more of these incidents happened.

841
01:06:25,182 --> 01:06:27,584
I just want you to think about that.

842
01:06:27,617 --> 01:06:29,986
You must have been there.

843
01:06:33,057 --> 01:06:35,092
But how could I have...

844
01:06:35,125 --> 01:06:36,393
How could I have done something

845
01:06:36,426 --> 01:06:39,429
and have absolutely no recollection of it?

846
01:06:39,463 --> 01:06:43,367
Have you been experiencing
any unusual behavior recently?

847
01:06:44,768 --> 01:06:46,436
What kind of behavior?

848
01:06:48,172 --> 01:06:52,742
Blackouts, dizzy spells, sleepwalking perhaps?

849
01:06:55,712 --> 01:06:57,381
Have you been sleepwalking?

850
01:06:59,249 --> 01:07:02,186
No. No, I haven't.

851
01:07:08,092 --> 01:07:10,527
( knocks )

852
01:07:10,560 --> 01:07:13,797
- Miss Young?
- Yes.

853
01:07:13,830 --> 01:07:18,168
- You're working pretty late.
- Yes?

854
01:07:18,202 --> 01:07:22,439
I'm Detective Spencer... Rick Spencer.

855
01:07:24,341 --> 01:07:27,043
You have a friend...
Patrick Costello. Is that correct?

856
01:07:28,778 --> 01:07:30,747
Yes.

857
01:07:30,780 --> 01:07:34,351
Yeah well, we're conducting an investigation.

858
01:07:34,384 --> 01:07:36,853
I'm wondering if maybe you could give us a hand.

859
01:07:36,886 --> 01:07:38,488
Of course.

860
01:07:38,522 --> 01:07:40,657
It's a murder investigation, Miss Young.

861
01:07:40,690 --> 01:07:43,093
The killer used a belt with
a pretty unusual buckle.

862
01:07:43,127 --> 01:07:44,394
It's a little something like that.

863
01:07:44,428 --> 01:07:46,430
You ever seen that buckle before?

864
01:07:49,133 --> 01:07:50,834
No, I've never seen anything like this.

865
01:07:50,867 --> 01:07:53,403
And you've never seen Patrick
Costello wearing something

866
01:07:53,437 --> 01:07:54,838
even remotely similar to this, huh?

867
01:07:54,871 --> 01:07:57,507
No.

868
01:07:58,808 --> 01:08:01,411
Well, I guess that’s that then.

869
01:08:01,445 --> 01:08:03,547
Listen, if you think of anything,

870
01:08:03,580 --> 01:08:05,482
anything at all, please give me a call.

871
01:08:05,515 --> 01:08:08,118
- Okay.
- Get some sleep.

872
01:08:08,152 --> 01:08:10,587
- Thank you.
- Good night.

873
01:08:21,865 --> 01:08:24,568
Nick: Bail's set at $25,000.

874
01:08:24,601 --> 01:08:27,671
Yeah, so what I’m wondering is...

875
01:08:27,704 --> 01:08:29,639
Are you crazy?

876
01:08:29,673 --> 01:08:32,242
Come on, man, where am I
gonna get that kind of dough?

877
01:08:32,276 --> 01:08:34,678
You're the bail bondsman.

878
01:08:34,711 --> 01:08:38,882
Yeah, yeah, sure, same to you, pal.

879
01:08:38,915 --> 01:08:41,117
Jesus.

880
01:08:48,892 --> 01:08:51,361
( knocking at door )

881
01:08:52,429 --> 01:08:55,131
Jesus. Just a minute.

882
01:09:02,572 --> 01:09:04,174
Hi, can I help you?

883
01:09:04,208 --> 01:09:06,843
- You must be Nick.
- Yeah.

884
01:09:06,876 --> 01:09:10,847
- I'm Laurel. I'm Patrick's friend.
- Uh-huh.

885
01:09:10,880 --> 01:09:15,519
- Can I ask you something about Patrick?
- Yeah sure.

886
01:09:16,886 --> 01:09:21,358
He said that he had some kind of psychic powers.

887
01:09:21,391 --> 01:09:23,393
Is that true?

888
01:09:29,766 --> 01:09:31,735
He must like you a lot.

889
01:09:31,768 --> 01:09:35,205
He doesn't talk about this with anyone.

890
01:09:42,846 --> 01:09:46,316
See, this thing happened when we were kids.

891
01:09:46,350 --> 01:09:47,817
It really messed him up.

892
01:09:47,851 --> 01:09:52,422
This girl we went to school with was murdered.

893
01:09:52,456 --> 01:09:56,926
The cops figured that Patrick could help them out.

894
01:09:56,960 --> 01:09:58,595
So he did his thing, you know?

895
01:09:58,628 --> 01:10:00,397
They gave him some of the stuff

896
01:10:00,430 --> 01:10:01,998
she was wearing at the time

897
01:10:02,031 --> 01:10:05,502
and he told them who the killer was.

898
01:10:06,870 --> 01:10:09,005
Mr. Solomon... Real nice guy.

899
01:10:09,038 --> 01:10:11,808
No one could believe it...

900
01:10:11,841 --> 01:10:14,444
Until they found out that Mr. Solomon

901
01:10:14,478 --> 01:10:16,446
had been having an affair with Audrey...

902
01:10:16,480 --> 01:10:18,815
That's her name.

903
01:10:18,848 --> 01:10:20,717
She was underage.

904
01:10:22,051 --> 01:10:25,389
Solomon kept insisting he was innocent

905
01:10:25,422 --> 01:10:28,258
and he said he wanted to take a lie detector test.

906
01:10:29,993 --> 01:10:32,862
The morning that he was going to take the test

907
01:10:32,896 --> 01:10:35,632
they found him dead.

908
01:10:35,665 --> 01:10:37,967
He hanged himself.

909
01:10:38,001 --> 01:10:40,970
Then about a month later,
they found this other guy,

910
01:10:41,004 --> 01:10:43,940
a transient.

911
01:10:43,973 --> 01:10:46,610
They found things on him that
sort of linked him to the murder.

912
01:10:46,643 --> 01:10:49,879
And then he made a confession, a full confession.

913
01:10:49,913 --> 01:10:52,649
He was confessing to a lot of things though.

914
01:10:52,682 --> 01:10:56,986
Patrick blamed himself, you know, for Mr. Solomon.

915
01:10:57,020 --> 01:11:01,658
But he said he was so sure, you know?

916
01:11:01,691 --> 01:11:03,527
As soon as we graduated, all he wanted to do

917
01:11:03,560 --> 01:11:07,331
was get out of town, you know, where no one knew.

918
01:11:07,364 --> 01:11:10,700
I think you're the first person
he’s told about it actually.

919
01:11:13,036 --> 01:11:14,871
( sighs )

920
01:11:19,509 --> 01:11:21,445
Thanks for telling me, Nick.

921
01:11:21,478 --> 01:11:23,747
Yeah.

922
01:11:23,780 --> 01:11:26,683
( police radio chatter )

923
01:11:26,716 --> 01:11:29,653
- Ricky, you coming or what?
- Huh? No, no.

924
01:11:29,686 --> 01:11:31,855
I'm gonna stick around. I'll see you tomorrow.

925
01:11:31,888 --> 01:11:34,324
Come on. I'm buying.

926
01:11:34,358 --> 01:11:36,693
( laughs )
What, you buying?

927
01:11:36,726 --> 01:11:39,863
Nah, sorry. Rain check.

928
01:11:39,896 --> 01:11:41,998
What is it?

929
01:11:42,031 --> 01:11:44,033
Nothing.

930
01:11:45,869 --> 01:11:47,871
( sighs )
I don't know, Adam.

931
01:11:47,904 --> 01:11:49,373
Don't you think the whole thing's

932
01:11:49,406 --> 01:11:50,974
falling into place a little too damn easy?

933
01:11:51,007 --> 01:11:55,579
Ricky, never ever complain
about anything being too easy.

934
01:11:55,612 --> 01:11:57,714
You hear what I'm saying?

935
01:11:57,747 --> 01:11:59,916
Yeah, I hear what you're saying.
Let me ask you this.

936
01:11:59,949 --> 01:12:03,353
Do you really think this kid
Costello is a serial killer?

937
01:12:03,387 --> 01:12:06,022
( laughs )
Hell no.

938
01:12:06,055 --> 01:12:08,825
But I think he killed April Harris,

939
01:12:08,858 --> 01:12:10,960
and that's good enough.

940
01:12:13,162 --> 01:12:15,665
I'll see you in the morning.

941
01:12:15,699 --> 01:12:17,767
Yeah.

942
01:12:21,004 --> 01:12:23,507
( sighs )

943
01:12:24,908 --> 01:12:27,043
( phone rings )

944
01:12:28,478 --> 01:12:29,913
Homicide, Spencer.

945
01:12:29,946 --> 01:12:32,015
- Woman: Detective Spencer?
- Yeah.

946
01:12:32,048 --> 01:12:33,917
I live across from Slater Park

947
01:12:33,950 --> 01:12:36,486
and I'm calling about the girl
that was found dead there.

948
01:12:36,520 --> 01:12:38,655
Uh-huh. What do you know about her?

949
01:12:38,688 --> 01:12:40,824
Well, I think I saw the guy who left her there,

950
01:12:40,857 --> 01:12:42,626
and I took his license plate number.

951
01:12:42,659 --> 01:12:44,528
Hold on a second, please. Hey, Adam, hold up!

952
01:12:44,561 --> 01:12:45,962
Okay, you wanna give it to me, please?

953
01:12:45,995 --> 01:12:47,964
( chatter )

954
01:12:47,997 --> 01:12:50,467
( keys jingling )

955
01:12:50,500 --> 01:12:53,136
Rise and shine, kid. You're out of here.

956
01:12:53,169 --> 01:12:55,939
- What?
- Yeah, we got the killer.

957
01:12:55,972 --> 01:12:58,475
The guy's name is Francis Crocket.

958
01:12:58,508 --> 01:12:59,843
He's a registered sex offender

959
01:12:59,876 --> 01:13:02,512
and we got an eyewitness that
puts him at the scene of the crime

960
01:13:02,546 --> 01:13:04,681
right about the time April Harris was killed.

961
01:13:04,714 --> 01:13:06,683
Look, just because you
found this guy near the body

962
01:13:06,716 --> 01:13:08,051
doesn't mean he’s the guy who did it.

963
01:13:08,084 --> 01:13:09,953
We've got forensic evidence that places her

964
01:13:09,986 --> 01:13:12,556
in Crocket's car that same evening.

965
01:13:12,589 --> 01:13:16,460
- Oh yeah? What kind of evidence?
- What are you, a cop?

966
01:13:16,493 --> 01:13:18,061
We got a hair sample, for one thing.

967
01:13:18,094 --> 01:13:20,063
And as an added bonus,

968
01:13:20,096 --> 01:13:22,031
we got a complete confession from the guy

969
01:13:22,065 --> 01:13:24,200
not only to the Harris case,
but to three others as well.

970
01:13:24,233 --> 01:13:27,003
Some sick shit, but there it is. You coming?

971
01:13:28,972 --> 01:13:32,776
It turns out he's one of Dr. Steering's patients.

972
01:13:32,809 --> 01:13:35,111
- Hey, Sammy.
- Hey, what's happening?

973
01:13:38,214 --> 01:13:40,116
Huh?

974
01:13:40,149 --> 01:13:42,952
That's one seriously screwed-up human being.

975
01:13:45,021 --> 01:13:47,090
Could have been you, kid. Come on, let's go.

976
01:14:10,714 --> 01:14:12,882
- Hi, I've just come to see Miss Young.
- ( elevator dings )

977
01:14:12,916 --> 01:14:14,918
Sure.

978
01:14:16,986 --> 01:14:18,922
Hello, Patrick.

979
01:14:18,955 --> 01:14:20,890
Detective Markowitz just called

980
01:14:20,924 --> 01:14:22,826
and told me the news.

981
01:14:22,859 --> 01:14:24,861
Yeah, they finally caught the guy.

982
01:14:24,894 --> 01:14:28,665
Yes, so they did.

983
01:14:28,698 --> 01:14:31,134
Well, congratulations.

984
01:14:31,167 --> 01:14:33,670
On your release I mean.

985
01:14:39,909 --> 01:14:42,779
( door closes )

986
01:14:42,812 --> 01:14:45,148
- Laurel.
- In here.

987
01:14:45,181 --> 01:14:47,216
I don't know if I should take this sweater or not.

988
01:14:47,250 --> 01:14:49,819
How cold does it getup in the
mountains at night anyway?

989
01:14:49,853 --> 01:14:52,956
I really wouldn't know. I haven't been there.

990
01:14:52,989 --> 01:14:55,925
Oh, I thought you were Ted.

991
01:15:00,096 --> 01:15:02,799
I heard about what happened.

992
01:15:02,832 --> 01:15:05,268
It must have been hard on you.

993
01:15:05,301 --> 01:15:08,605
Yeah, well, it wasn’t a whole lot of fun actually.

994
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:15,712
No, not just now. I meant before.

995
01:15:15,745 --> 01:15:17,981
Nick told me about Audrey.

996
01:15:19,749 --> 01:15:22,018
He told you about Audrey?

997
01:15:23,352 --> 01:15:25,589
( sighs )

998
01:15:26,790 --> 01:15:28,992
Did he tell you the whole story?

999
01:15:29,025 --> 01:15:31,961
Well, yes. I...

1000
01:15:31,995 --> 01:15:34,230
What I mean is did he tell you her last name?

1001
01:15:34,263 --> 01:15:37,567
No, huh?

1002
01:15:37,601 --> 01:15:42,038
Her last name was Costello. She was my sister.

1003
01:15:42,071 --> 01:15:43,873
Look, just forget it, all right?

1004
01:15:43,907 --> 01:15:45,942
It's ancient history.

1005
01:15:45,975 --> 01:15:48,612
Patrick, I'm so sorry.

1006
01:15:51,615 --> 01:15:54,050
I gotta go. I'll see you around.

1007
01:15:54,083 --> 01:15:56,019
Patrick, don't do this.

1008
01:15:56,052 --> 01:15:59,055
"Don't do this"? I'm not doing anything.

1009
01:15:59,088 --> 01:16:02,225
Look, you're free to do
whatever it is you wanna do.

1010
01:16:02,258 --> 01:16:05,729
Just take the sweater. He'll love it.

1011
01:16:07,130 --> 01:16:11,334
( door opens, closes )

1012
01:16:19,042 --> 01:16:21,044
( dog barks )

1013
01:16:36,259 --> 01:16:38,795
God, it's beautiful.

1014
01:16:44,668 --> 01:16:47,671
( classical music playing )

1015
01:16:52,075 --> 01:16:54,077
Good evening. I'm Dr. Steering.

1016
01:16:54,110 --> 01:16:55,378
I'm here for the symposium.

1017
01:16:55,411 --> 01:16:57,080
Ah, Dr. Steering,

1018
01:16:57,113 --> 01:16:58,915
it's a pleasure to have you here again, sir.

1019
01:16:58,948 --> 01:17:01,985
The only cottage we have left now is number 16.

1020
01:17:02,018 --> 01:17:04,187
That's about half a mile down the road.

1021
01:17:04,220 --> 01:17:05,955
If you'd prefer a double suite,

1022
01:17:05,989 --> 01:17:07,891
I'm sure we can arrange it at a similar price.

1023
01:17:07,924 --> 01:17:09,192
What do you think?

1024
01:17:09,225 --> 01:17:10,927
You wanna trek down the road a half a mile

1025
01:17:10,960 --> 01:17:12,862
or you wanna stay here in the lodge?

1026
01:17:12,896 --> 01:17:15,364
- It sounds fine. The cottage sounds fine.
- Okay.

1027
01:17:15,398 --> 01:17:17,233
All right, so you’ve been preregistered.

1028
01:17:17,266 --> 01:17:19,435
All I'll require is your
credit card for an imprint.

1029
01:17:19,468 --> 01:17:21,805
- Thank you.
- ( Laurel clears throat )

1030
01:17:30,079 --> 01:17:32,882
All right, Doctor.

1031
01:17:32,916 --> 01:17:35,184
- Doctor?
- Thank you.

1032
01:17:37,086 --> 01:17:39,889
- ( train horn blaring )
- ( sighs )

1033
01:17:52,001 --> 01:17:53,002
( screams )

1034
01:17:54,871 --> 01:17:56,472
( gasping )

1035
01:17:56,505 --> 01:17:59,342
( women choking )

1036
01:18:22,398 --> 01:18:24,868
Ted: Far from the madding crowd.

1037
01:18:24,901 --> 01:18:28,404
No telephone, no television.

1038
01:18:28,437 --> 01:18:30,740
Yuh! No central heating.

1039
01:18:30,774 --> 01:18:32,909
- ( laughs )
- Look at this.

1040
01:18:32,942 --> 01:18:34,477
Can't wait to get into this.

1041
01:18:34,510 --> 01:18:36,813
- Eh, well.
- Oh, it's lovely.

1042
01:18:38,815 --> 01:18:41,450
And the living room... Wait till you see this.

1043
01:18:43,052 --> 01:18:45,321
Upstairs are the bedrooms.

1044
01:18:46,489 --> 01:18:47,991
Nice, huh?

1045
01:18:50,960 --> 01:18:53,897
We have our choice of sleeping accommodations.

1046
01:18:57,033 --> 01:18:59,102
You like it?

1047
01:19:00,970 --> 01:19:02,972
It's great.

1048
01:19:10,079 --> 01:19:13,449
( wind howling )

1049
01:19:23,526 --> 01:19:27,096
( sighs )

1050
01:19:32,969 --> 01:19:36,205
- Are you cold?
- No.

1051
01:19:42,411 --> 01:19:44,413
Ted...

1052
01:19:46,149 --> 01:19:48,952
I don't know if I'm ready for this.

1053
01:19:51,988 --> 01:19:53,589
I understand.

1054
01:19:53,622 --> 01:19:55,091
I want to be here with you, but...

1055
01:19:55,124 --> 01:19:59,929
Laurel, you don’t have to explain, okay?

1056
01:20:03,532 --> 01:20:06,202
Oh boy, let's see what we've got here.

1057
01:20:06,235 --> 01:20:08,471
I brought something to warm us up a bit.

1058
01:20:10,606 --> 01:20:13,076
Uh-huh.

1059
01:20:15,411 --> 01:20:19,482
A 1985 Bordeaux. Does that sound good?

1060
01:20:19,515 --> 01:20:21,985
Sounds great.

1061
01:20:32,528 --> 01:20:34,330
Hi, yes, this is an emergency.

1062
01:20:34,363 --> 01:20:38,034
I'm trying to reach Dr. Theodore Steering.

1063
01:20:38,067 --> 01:20:40,569
Yeah.

1064
01:20:40,603 --> 01:20:44,407
Uh-huh. Green Peaks?

1065
01:20:44,440 --> 01:20:47,376
Uh-huh. How do I get there?

1066
01:21:00,023 --> 01:21:02,391
( engine starts )

1067
01:21:06,129 --> 01:21:09,598
It has nothing to do with male-female positioning.

1068
01:21:09,632 --> 01:21:11,600
I still don't agree.

1069
01:21:11,634 --> 01:21:14,003
I think your paper is an apology

1070
01:21:14,037 --> 01:21:15,538
for the male point of view.

1071
01:21:17,006 --> 01:21:19,042
( chuckling )

1072
01:21:19,075 --> 01:21:20,944
That's not what it is at all.

1073
01:21:20,977 --> 01:21:22,979
It's a summary of the current research

1074
01:21:23,012 --> 01:21:25,448
into the psychopathology of sexual violence.

1075
01:21:25,481 --> 01:21:28,551
I'm not... I'm not even sure
that I believe in it myself.

1076
01:21:28,584 --> 01:21:31,487
But then why would you encourage
others to believe in it?

1077
01:21:31,520 --> 01:21:35,158
I... Laurel, I am not encouraging
anybody to believe anything.

1078
01:21:35,191 --> 01:21:38,061
I'm presenting statistics.

1079
01:21:38,094 --> 01:21:41,364
Look, Laurel,

1080
01:21:41,397 --> 01:21:44,267
psychology is a very cynical business.

1081
01:21:47,971 --> 01:21:50,206
And I suggest that if you want
to pursue this any further

1082
01:21:50,239 --> 01:21:52,308
that we get another bottle of wine.

1083
01:21:52,341 --> 01:21:53,977
I'll get it.

1084
01:21:54,010 --> 01:21:57,480
But, Ted, your humor is no defense.

1085
01:21:57,513 --> 01:22:00,049
- You all right?
- I'm sorry.

1086
01:22:00,083 --> 01:22:02,018
Serves you right for talking about my humor.

1087
01:22:02,051 --> 01:22:03,987
( laughs )
So...

1088
01:22:04,020 --> 01:22:05,989
Anyway, what I'm trying to say

1089
01:22:06,022 --> 01:22:09,625
is the mindset of modern
psychology is male dominant.

1090
01:22:09,658 --> 01:22:14,130
It's time fora female
perspective to be acknowledged.

1091
01:22:17,166 --> 01:22:20,269
Believe me, there's nothing more interesting to me

1092
01:22:20,303 --> 01:22:22,305
than the female perspective.

1093
01:22:30,179 --> 01:22:32,515
Talk to me.

1094
01:22:34,317 --> 01:22:37,686
Talk to me about female perspective.

1095
01:22:37,720 --> 01:22:39,722
I'm all ears.

1096
01:22:42,358 --> 01:22:44,527
I think we should clean up.

1097
01:22:47,263 --> 01:22:50,166
Dirty dishes are not a defense, Laurel.

1098
01:22:57,606 --> 01:23:00,409
Laurel, what are you doing?

1099
01:23:00,443 --> 01:23:02,445
I want to hear what you have to say.

1100
01:23:16,525 --> 01:23:19,528
I want to hear all about the female perspective.

1101
01:23:32,808 --> 01:23:35,010
Stop please!

1102
01:23:36,845 --> 01:23:40,049
- Ah!
- ( tires screech )

1103
01:23:47,223 --> 01:23:49,225
( horn blares )

1104
01:23:52,495 --> 01:23:56,199
( horn blaring )

1105
01:24:07,343 --> 01:24:09,812
Tell me about Patrick Costello.

1106
01:24:12,748 --> 01:24:14,750
What do you mean?

1107
01:24:16,319 --> 01:24:18,354
You like him, don't you?

1108
01:24:18,387 --> 01:24:21,457
- ( cork pops )
- Yes.

1109
01:24:34,203 --> 01:24:36,305
Are you in love with him?

1110
01:24:38,274 --> 01:24:40,809
No.

1111
01:24:40,843 --> 01:24:43,812
You're not?

1112
01:24:43,846 --> 01:24:45,848
No.

1113
01:24:48,584 --> 01:24:50,419
Good.

1114
01:24:58,594 --> 01:25:01,130
What are your feelings about me?

1115
01:25:10,273 --> 01:25:12,708
- Ted...
- No, wait.

1116
01:25:15,778 --> 01:25:18,914
Do you, ahem...

1117
01:25:18,947 --> 01:25:22,385
Do you think that you could love me?

1118
01:25:22,418 --> 01:25:24,387
( sighs )

1119
01:25:24,420 --> 01:25:28,191
You know, this wine has
definitely gotten to my head.

1120
01:25:28,224 --> 01:25:29,692
I think I should go to bed.

1121
01:25:29,725 --> 01:25:33,196
- ( bottle breaks )
- Stay right here and answer me.

1122
01:25:34,363 --> 01:25:36,265
Damn it, answer me!

1123
01:25:36,299 --> 01:25:37,566
( glass breaks )

1124
01:25:46,275 --> 01:25:48,244
That wasn't nice, Laurel.

1125
01:25:48,277 --> 01:25:50,546
Come on.

1126
01:26:00,256 --> 01:26:02,591
- Stop, stop, please!
- ( tires screech )

1127
01:26:02,625 --> 01:26:04,227
Uh!

1128
01:26:09,698 --> 01:26:11,834
We've gotta get out of here.

1129
01:26:11,867 --> 01:26:13,869
Get in the car, quick.

1130
01:26:23,011 --> 01:26:25,214
( engine sputtering )

1131
01:26:27,015 --> 01:26:29,218
Ah!

1132
01:26:29,252 --> 01:26:31,754
- No!
- Leave us alone!

1133
01:26:31,787 --> 01:26:34,890
Laurel: No!

1134
01:26:34,923 --> 01:26:36,825
Patrick!

1135
01:26:36,859 --> 01:26:38,761
( screaming )

1136
01:26:38,794 --> 01:26:40,596
- Please help me.
- No!

1137
01:26:40,629 --> 01:26:42,231
- Please! Please help me.
- No!

1138
01:26:42,265 --> 01:26:44,500
( grunts )

1139
01:27:09,892 --> 01:27:12,528
( gasps )

1140
01:27:12,561 --> 01:27:14,797
( grunts )

1141
01:27:18,033 --> 01:27:20,569
( screams )

1142
01:27:32,415 --> 01:27:35,250
( honking horn )

1143
01:27:37,720 --> 01:27:39,355
Patrick!

1144
01:27:40,856 --> 01:27:42,858
Ah!

1145
01:28:01,477 --> 01:28:03,379
Patrick!

1146
01:28:04,513 --> 01:28:07,015
- Patrick!
- What?

1147
01:28:10,052 --> 01:28:11,654
You okay?

1148
01:28:11,687 --> 01:28:14,022
- Oh yeah, fine.
- Come on, sit over here.

1149
01:28:14,056 --> 01:28:16,392
I almost got run over by a snowplow.

1150
01:28:16,425 --> 01:28:17,926
Never felt better.

1151
01:28:17,960 --> 01:28:20,062
How are you? You okay?

1152
01:28:20,095 --> 01:28:22,064
Never felt better.

1153
01:28:22,097 --> 01:28:24,433
- Ah!
- Oh, sorry.

1154
01:28:24,467 --> 01:28:26,869
I gotta tell you something.

1155
01:28:26,902 --> 01:28:28,837
I hate Chinese food.

1156
01:28:28,871 --> 01:28:30,839
And you know that classical music?

1157
01:28:30,873 --> 01:28:32,575
- I hate that too.
- ( laughs )

1158
01:28:32,608 --> 01:28:36,712
Please don't make me listen to
that Bach guy anymore, okay?

1159
01:28:36,745 --> 01:28:38,747
Okay.

